13lackHawk 27-Jul-18 06:59 AM
hey, I have some problems with particles again I have one shitty model with wrong rotation on the left part of screenshot. I want to turn it 90 degrees and make it continiously rotate like I show on the right part of screenshot. what operators/initialazers/parameters I should use for that?
Toyoka 27-Jul-18 08:07 AM
there's an initializer you can use to give the model the proper rotation: Rotation Random. Make sure min and max are the same number if you want a specific rotation (0-360) out of it. (edited)
alternatively, if the model is supposed to be upright by default, you can go into the "render models" renderer and there should be two properties: ignore normal and orient model to z normal
enabling one of them should orient the model to the proper rotation
13lackHawk 27-Jul-18 08:09 AM
got it, thanks!
Toyoka 27-Jul-18 08:10 AM
and to have it rotate constantly, you might want Ramp Scalar Linear Simple and set it to "Roll" or "Yaw" or "Pitch" depending on how it rotates.
making sure to set "End Time" to something high like 999999
